'''Joe Shmoe''' (also spelled '''Joe Schmoe''') is one of the most commonly used fictional names.  Adding a "Shm" to the beginning of a word is meant to diminish, negate, or dismiss an argument.  This process was adapted in English from the use of the "Shm" prefix in several [[Yiddish language|Yiddish]] words that have negative meanings.

